author: The Leader staff
title: CCC sweeps Onondaga
text: Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 11:10 PM Updated at 11:10 PM By The Leader staff Posted Oct. 7, 2015 at 11:10 PM CORNING | Amber Edwards and Jordan Raupers combined for 17 kills Wednesday to lead Corning Community College to a 25-18, 25-15, 25-20 sweep of Onondaga. Edwards registered a team-best nine kills and also led the Red Barons with five blocks. Raupers tallied eight kills, dished out 16 setter assists and had five digs. Corning also got seven kills and three digs from Alyssa Mosher. At the service line, CCCâ€™s Whitney Hauptman recorded two aces and also chipped in with 13 setter assists. The Red Barons got additional contributions from Sarah Heveland (team-best 11 digs), Angelena Maio (three kills, nine digs), Kaitlyn Weaver (four kills, one ace) and Angie Frampton (four kills, one block). With the victory, Corning improved to 20-4 and 5-0 in the MSAC. The Red Barons will host Cayuga at 6 p.m. Wednesday. By The Leader staff
